the_silver_searcher
------------------------------------------
A code searching tool similar to ack, with a focus on speed.

 - It searches code about 3-5x faster than ack.
 - It ignores file patterns from your .gitignore and .hgignore.
 - If there are files in your source repo you don't want to search, just add
   their patterns to a .agignore file. *cough* extern *cough*
 - The command name is 33% shorter than ack, and all keys are on the home row!

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.7.32-1
  liblzma5-5.0.5-1
  libpcre1-8.34-1
  zlib0-1.2.8-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.24.51-5
  cygport-0.17.0-1
  gcc-core-4.9.0-1
  make-4.0-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/ggreer/the_silver_searcher

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/ggreer/the_silver_searcher/archive/0.24.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack the_silver_searcher-0.24.1-X-src.tar.xz
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
        unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./the_silver_searcher-0.24.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/the_silver_searcher-0.24.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/the_silver_searcher-0.24.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(the_silver_searcher)
  /usr/bin/ag.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/the_silver_searcher.README
  /usr/share/doc/the_silver_searcher/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/the_silver_searcher/NOTICE
  /usr/share/man/man1/ag.1.gz
  /usr/share/the_silver_searcher/completions/ag.bashcomp.sh

